The paper deals with learning ontologies from text data, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to learn representations and make predictions, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of constraints and partial order structures, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
